data.name: PSet.Name[10OhK0qVmHuO00025QrE$V]
data.value: Pset_ProtectiveDeviceTrippingUnitTypeElectroMagnetic

data.name: PSet.Definition[10OhK0qVmHuO00025QrE$V]
data.value: Information on tripping units that are electrically or magnetically tripped.

data.name: Property.ElectroMagneticTrippingUnitType.Name[15l$_0qVmHuO00025QrE$V]
data.value: ElectroMagneticTrippingUnitType

data.name: Property.ElectroMagneticTrippingUnitType.Definition[15l$_0qVmHuO00025QrE$V]
data.value: A list of the available types of electric magnetic tripping unit from which that required may be selected. These cover overload, none special, short circuit, motor protection and bi-metal tripping.

data.name: Property.I1.Name[1LFqY0qVmHuO00025QrE$V]
data.value: I1

data.name: Property.I1.Definition[1LFqY0qVmHuO00025QrE$V]
data.value: The (thermal) lower testing current limit in [x In], indicating that for currents lower than I1, the tripping time shall be longer than the associated tripping time, T2.

data.name: Property.I2.Name[1RDIc0qVmHuO00025QrE$V]
data.value: I2

data.name: Property.I2.Definition[1RDIc0qVmHuO00025QrE$V]
data.value: The (thermal) upper testing current limit in [x In], indicating that for currents larger than I2, the tripping time shall be shorter than the associated tripping time, T2.

data.name: Property.T2.Name[1WadG0qVmHuO00025QrE$V]
data.value: T2

data.name: Property.T2.Definition[1WadG0qVmHuO00025QrE$V]
data.value: The (thermal) testing time in [s] associated with the testing currents I1 and I2.

data.name: Property.DefinedTemperature.Name[1eKXY0qVmHuO00025QrE$V]
data.value: DefinedTemperature

data.name: Property.DefinedTemperature.Definition[1eKXY0qVmHuO00025QrE$V]
data.value: The ambient temperature at which the thermal current/time-curve associated with this protection device is defined.

data.name: Property.TemperatureFactor.Name[1ku900qVmHuO00025QrE$V]
data.value: TemperatureFactor

data.name: Property.TemperatureFactor.Definition[1ku900qVmHuO00025QrE$V]
data.value: The correction factor (typically measured as %/deg K) for adjusting the thermal current/time to an ambient temperature different from the value given by the defined temperature.

data.name: Property.I4.Name[1pfKG0qVmHuO00025QrE$V]
data.value: I4

data.name: Property.I4.Definition[1pfKG0qVmHuO00025QrE$V]
data.value: The lower electromagnetic testing current limit in [x In], indicating that for currents lower than I4, the tripping time shall be longer than the associated tripping time, T5, i.e. the device shall not trip instantaneous.

data.name: Property.I5.Name[1vcoK0qVmHuO00025QrE$V]
data.value: I5

data.name: Property.I5.Definition[1vcoK0qVmHuO00025QrE$V]
data.value: The upper electromagnetic testing current limit in [x In], indicating that for currents larger than I5, the tripping time shall be shorter than or equal to the associated tripping time, T5, i.e. the device shall trip instantaneous.

data.name: Property.T5.Name[20APo0qVmHuO00025QrE$V]
data.value: T5

data.name: Property.T5.Definition[20APo0qVmHuO00025QrE$V]
data.value: The electromagnetic testing time in [s] associated with the testing currents I4 and I5, i.e. electromagnetic tripping time

data.name: Property.CurveDesignation.Name[24xb20qVmHuO00025QrE$V]
data.value: CurveDesignation

data.name: Property.CurveDesignation.Definition[24xb20qVmHuO00025QrE$V]
data.value: The designation of the trippingcurve given by the manufacturer. For a MCB the designation should be in accordance with the designations given in IEC 60898.
